[[File:ArnoldSchwarzeneggerDec09.jpg|thumb|right|alt=Man wearing a blue suit and standing at a podium. He is facing away from the camera, smiling, and is clapping.|Arnold Schwarzenegger in December 2009 speaking at a ceremony for [[James Cameron]] to receive a star on the [[Hollywood Walk of Fame]]]]
{{Arnold Schwarzenegger series}}
'''[[Arnold Schwarzenegger|Arnold Alois Schwarzenegger]]''' is an Austrian–American actor, director, film producer, politician and former professional bodybuilder who has appeared in over 35 films, and has also ventured into directing and producing. Schwarzenegger began his acting career primarily with small roles in film and television starting in 1969. For his first film role, he was credited as "Arnold Strong", but was credited with his birth name thereafter. He has appeared mainly in [[action film|action]] and [[comedy film|comedy]] films.<ref name="EWBioTotalRecall">{{cite news|last=Chase |first=Donald |title=A Hard Man is Good to Film |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=June 8, 1990 |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,317552,00.html |accessdate=February 19, 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ritDQUbU?url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0%2C%2C317552%2C00.html |archivedate=2010-08-04 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> In addition to films and television, he has appeared in music videos for [[AC/DC]], [[Bon Jovi]], and [[Guns N' Roses]].
In the 1980s, Schwarzenegger became his primary character in two&nbsp;film franchises: as [[Conan the Barbarian|Conan]] in the ''Conan'' series and as [[Terminator (character)|The Terminator]] in the [[Terminator (franchise)|''Terminator'' series]]. His other film roles include ''[[Commando (1985 film)|Commando]]'', ''[[The Running Man (1987 film)|The Running Man]]'', ''[[Predator (film)|Predator]]'', ''[[Total Recall (1990 film)|Total Recall]]'', ''[[Last Action Hero]]'' and ''[[True Lies]]''. Although Schwarzenegger's acting career was put on hiatus due to his position as [[Governor of California]], he also made several cameos in various films while in office, including ''[[The Kid & I]]'' and ''[[The Expendables (2010 film)|The Expendables]]''.<ref name="ExpendSlyCameo">{{cite news|title=Guv to Shoot Action Film Amid Budget Drama |publisher=[[NBC News]] |date=February 19, 2009 |url=http://www.nbclosangeles.com/news/entertainment/Guv-to-Shoot-Action-Film-Amid-Budget-Drama.html |accessdate=February 19, 2009 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ritRHGb5?url=http://www.nbclosangeles.com/entertainment/celebrity/Guv-to-Shoot-Action-Film-Amid-Budget-Drama.html |archivedate=August 4, 2010 |deadurl=no |df= }}</ref> On February 11, 2011, just over a month after leaving office, Schwarzenegger announced he would return to acting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.msn.com/movies/article.aspx?news=628473&GT1=28101 |title=Schwarzenegger says he's returning to acting |publisher=[[MSN]] |date=February 11, 2011 |accessdate=February 11, 2011}}</ref>
Schwarzenegger has received several awards and nominations for his work in films. In ''[[Stay Hungry]]'', one of his early roles, he won a [[Golden Globe Award]] for Best Acting Debut in a Motion Picture. He has also been nominated for various awards for his roles in ''[[Terminator 2: Judgment Day]]'', ''[[Junior (1994 film)|Junior]]'', and ''True Lies''. According to [[Box Office Mojo]], a box office revenue tracking website, films in which Schwarzenegger has acted have grossed a total of more than [[United States dollar|$]]1.7&nbsp;billion within the United States, with an average of $67&nbsp;million per film and total [[United States dollar|$]]4.0&nbsp;billion worldwide.<ref name="BOXMOJO">{{cite news|url=http://boxofficemojo.com/people/chart/?id=arnoldschwarzenegger.htm|title=Arnold Schwarzenegger|publisher=[[Box Office Mojo]]|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref> According to The Numbers, another box office revenue tracking website, films in which Schwarzenegger has acted have total grossed around [[United States dollar|$]]4.5&nbsp;billion worldwide.<ref name="TheNumbers">{{cite news|url=http://www.the-numbers.com/person/128750401-Arnold-Schwarzenegger|title=Arnold Schwarzenegger|publisher=The Numbers|accessdate=February 20, 2014}}</ref>
