'''Agustin Bostani''' (29 November 1876 in Dair al-Qamar, [[Lebanon]] &ndash; 30 October 1957) was an [[eparch]] of the [[Maronite Catholic Eparchy of Sidon]].
Bostani was on April 20, 1899 ordained to the priesthood. On February 23, 1919 he was appointed Eparch of Sidon and on March 2, 1919 the [[List of Maronite Patriarchs|Maronite Patriarch of Antioch]] [[Elias Peter Hoayek]] consecrated him bishop. Bostani was Eparch of Sidon more than 38 years and died on 30 October 1957<ref>[http://www.apostolische-nachfolge.de/nekrolog_1957.htm apostolische-nachfolge.de]</ref> at the age of 80.
