'''Tricia Devereaux''' (born January 12, 1975)<ref name=profile/> is the [[stage name]] of an American former [[pornographic actress]], [[XRCO Hall of Fame]] inductee, and co-owner of [[Evil Angel (studio)|Evil Angel]] studios.

==Career==
Devereaux was introduced to the [[adult industry]] when her then husband, Patrick, got a job working as a bouncer in a strip club and Devereaux would occasionally visit him there. The other dancers encouraged her to enter the club's amateur contest which she won; this led to her working there to make extra money.<ref name=oh />{{rp|554}} A number of established porn stars visited the club as feature dancers—names such as [[Victoria Paris]], [[Jeanna Fine]], and [[Samantha Strong]].<ref name=oh />{{rp|555}}

Seeing the extra money that the features made, Devereaux sent pictures of herself to ''[[Hustler]]'' magazine for their "Beaver Hunt" feature, which was published. At the same time Devereaux came in fifth in [[Déjà Vu (company)|Déjà Vu]]'s national Stripper of the Year. She then flew out to [[Los Angeles]] at [[Joey Silvera]]'s request (he had seen pictures Devereaux had sent of herself to [[Jim South]]), where she made her first on-camera scene with Silvera in ''Fashion Sluts 7''.<ref name=oh556>{{cite book|title=The Other Hollywood|page=556}}</ref>

In 1998, Devereaux was infected with [[HIV]] during a scene with [[Marc Wallice]].<ref name=ABCNews>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Health/AIDS/hiv-actors-positive-test-unsettles-hub-us-porn/story?id=11892877&page=3|title=HIV: Actor's Positive Test Unsettles Hub of U.S. Porn Industry  - ABC News|last=Jane E. Allen|date=2010-10-15|work=[[ABC News]]|page=3|accessdate=21 January 2011}}</ref>

Now known as Karen Stagliano, she is also the co-owner of [[Evil Angel (studio)|Evil Angel]], a production company, with her husband [[John Stagliano]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kernes|first=Mark|title=Free Speech Coalition Benefits From Hustler's Freedomfest Not so much actual sex, but plenty of drinks and rock 'n' roll|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/Free-Speech-Coalition-Benefits-From-Hustler-s-Freedomfest-354197.html|publisher=Adult Video News|accessdate=28 February 2014}}</ref>

==Awards==
