* 2003 AVN Award - Best Editing, Film (''The Fashionistas'') with John Stagliano{{citation needed|date=January 2015}}
* 2011 [[XRCO Hall of Fame]] inductee<ref>{{cite web|title=XRCO Announces 2011 Nominations|publisher=AVN.com|author=Peter Warren|url=http://business.avn.com/articles/video/XRCO-Announces-2011-Nominations-426791.html|accessdate=2011-02-26|date=2011-02-22}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Devereaux grew up "in a small town a couple hours outside of Chicago," where she had a strict upbringing and attended a private Catholic high school.<ref name=oh>{{cite book|last=McNeil|first=Legs|authorlink=Legs McNeil|author2=Jennifer Osborne |others=with Peter Pavia|title=The Other Hollywood: The Uncensored Oral History of the Porn Industry|year=2006|publisher=ReganBooks|location=New York|isbn=0-06-009660-8}}</ref>{{rp|552}}

She attended college in the Midwest, got her bachelor's degree in Biology<ref>{{cite web|url=http://excaliburfilms.com/pornlist/starpgs/Tricia_Devereaux.htm|title=Tricia Devereaux Biography|accessdate=2007-11-11|publisher=Excalibur Films}}</ref> from a college in [[Missouri]], then attended one year of medical school.<ref name=oh />{{rp|552}} Before starting medical school, she had married her boyfriend Patrick.<ref name=oh />{{rp|553}} After she had appeared in a number of films, Devereaux was dismissed from medical school after the school accused her of cheating on a test; Devereaux claims the charge was rigged and that the real reason she was dismissed was due to her involvement in pornography.<ref name=oh />{{rp|559}} Soon afterwards, Devereaux divorced her husband; she later said that "Patrick was too much of a pushover personality-wise, and we'd been having problems financially."<ref name=oh />{{rp|560}}

She married former [[Pornographic film actor|porn star]] and current director [[John Stagliano]] on November 26, 2008.<ref>{{cite web | title =John and Karen Stagliano Tie the Knot | author=Jared Rutter | publisher =AVN.com | url =http://www.avn.com/performer/articles/33766.html| date = 2008-12-13| accessdate =2008-12-11 }}</ref> She now is known as Karen Stagliano.<ref name=ABCNews />

